ol.li:
1. A hearing device configured to be worn in an ear of a user, the hearing device being configured to provide an audio signal to the user, the hearing device comprising:


a circuit assembly, comprising:


a printed circuit board assembly, comprising:


a first circuit board;

a second circuit board;

a third circuit board interconnected with the first circuit board and the second circuit board;


a battery, and

an output transducer for providing the audio signal, wherein the printed circuit board assembly is folded about the battery and the output transducer.

claim.claim-text:
A hearing device configured to be worn in an ear of a user, the hearing device being configured to provide an audio signal to the user, the hearing device comprising:
- a circuit assembly, comprising:
a printed circuit board assembly, comprising:
a first circuit board;
a second circuit board;
a third circuit board interconnected with the first circuit board and the second circuit board;
a battery, and
an output transducer for providing the audio signal, wherein the printed circuit board assembly is folded about the battery and the output transducer.
